<paragraph id="657636E63369FF9D2A64FB9F4ACFFB43" blockId="0.[851,1413,1148,1236]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">
<heading id="3E3E818A3369FF9D2A64FB9F4BE7FB23" bold="true" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" reason="2">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2A64FB9F4BE7FB23" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">
Nomenclature of 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2D2BFB9F4AC3FB03" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1052,1185,1148,1172]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D2BFB9F4AC3FB03" bold="true" box="[1052,1185,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2DE9FB9F4B1EFB04" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1831" box="[1246,1404,1148,1172]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Mithrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DE9FB9F4B1EFB04" bold="true" box="[1246,1404,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Mithrax asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: authorship, date of publication, and type species
</emphasis>
</heading>
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D1CFB5F4ACFFB43" bold="true" box="[1067,1197,1212,1236]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">designation</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DD3656D3369FF9F2A1AFB1F4C10FC42" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="657636E63369FF9F2A1AFB1F4C53FDC2" blockId="0.[813,1452,1276,2100]" lastBlockId="2.[113,753,189,597]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">
The date of publication of 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2D7FFB1F4AABFA83" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1096,1225,1276,1300]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D7FFB1F4AABFA83" box="[1096,1225,1276,1300]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was given as “1847” by 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A66FAFE4A5DFAA3" author="Ng PKL &amp; Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF" box="[849,1087,1308,1333]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref9117" refString="Ng PKL, Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">Ng et al. (2008: 118)</bibRefCitation>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2DF3FAFF4B27FAA3" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1220,1349,1308,1332]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DF3FAFF4B27FAA3" box="[1220,1349,1308,1332]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first used in 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2AB7FADF4A49FAC3" author="White A" box="[896,1067,1340,1364]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" refId="ref10132" refString="White A (1847) List of Specimens of Crustacea in the Collection of the British Museum. British Museum, London, viii + 143 pp. [April 1847 (Sherborn 1926: 272)]" type="book" year="1847">White (1847: 9)</bibRefCitation>
but as a 
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DBDFADE4B43FAC3" box="[1162,1313,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">nomen nudum</emphasis>
, and the two included species-group names were also 
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DD1FABE4B11FAE3" box="[1254,1395,1372,1396]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">nomina nuda</emphasis>
. The first publication to make the genus-group name 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2C1CFA9F4BCEFA03" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1323,1452,1404,1428]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2C1CFA9F4BCEFA03" box="[1323,1452,1404,1428]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available was actually White (1848: 222) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2C79FA7F4A68FA43" author="Clark PF &amp; Presswell B" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="149 - 166" refId="ref6824" refString="Clark PF &amp; Presswell B (2001) Adam White: The crustacean years. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 49 (1): 149 - 166." type="journal article" year="2001">Clark &amp; Presswell, 2001: 161</bibRefCitation>
). The authorship and date of publication for the widespread species 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2D7CFA3F4A80FA63" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1831" box="[1099,1250,1500,1524]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Mithrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D7CFA3F4A80FA63" box="[1099,1250,1500,1524]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Mithrax asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly cited as H. 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A58FA1F4ACBF983" author="Milne Edwards H" box="[879,1193,1532,1556]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" refId="ref8854" refString="Milne Edwards H (1834 a) Histoire naturelle des Crustaces, comprenant l'anatomie, la physiologie et la classification de ces animaux, Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, vol. 1, 468 pp." type="book" year="1834">Milne Edwards (1834a: 320)</bibRefCitation>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2DD0FA1F4BC5F983" author="Davie PJF" box="[1255,1447,1532,1556]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" refId="ref7035" refString="Davie PJF (2002) Crustacea: Malacostraca: Eucaridae (Part 2): Decapoda-Anomura, Brachyura. In: Wells A &amp; Houston WWK (eds.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Volume 19.3 B, CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, Australia, xiv + 641 pp." type="book" year="2002">Davie, 2002: 311</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A1AF9FE4A67F9A3" author="Ng PKL &amp; Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF" box="[813,1029,1564,1589]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref9117" refString="Ng PKL, Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">Ng et al., 2008: 118</bibRefCitation>
). The name is, however, available from H. 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A66F9DF4A2BF9C3" author="Milne Edwards H" box="[849,1097,1596,1620]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref8817" refString="Milne Edwards H (1831) Observations sur les Crustaces du genre Mithrax. Magasin de Zoologie, 2 (7): [1] - [16], pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1831">Milne Edwards (1831</bibRefCitation>
: [10]). 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2DA9F9DF4DB3F9E3" authority="H. Milne Edwards, 1831" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1831" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Mithrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DA9F9DF4B5EF9C3" box="[1182,1340,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Mithrax asper</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2C5CF9DF4DB3F9E3" author="Milne Edwards H" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref8817" refString="Milne Edwards H (1831) Observations sur les Crustaces du genre Mithrax. Magasin de Zoologie, 2 (7): [1] - [16], pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1831">Milne Edwards, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was first transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2DEDF9BF4D07F903" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DEDF9BF4B39F9E3" box="[1242,1371,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2AA1F99F4A02F903" author="Miers EJ" box="[918,1120,1660,1684]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="634 - 673" refId="ref8691" refString="Miers EJ (1879) On the classification of the maioid Crustacea or Oxyrhyncha, with a synopsis of the families, subfamilies and genera. Journal of the Linnean Society of London, Zoology, 14 (79): 634 - 673, pls. 12 - 13." type="journal article" year="1879">Miers (1879: 660)</bibRefCitation>
, who also designated it as the type species of the genus. While this has been followed by all subsequent workers, his action is invalid. 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2C24F95F4A59F963" authority="H. Milne Edwards, 1831" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1831" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Mithrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2C24F95F4BC9F943" box="[1299,1451,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Mithrax asper</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A78F93F4A59F963" author="Milne Edwards H" box="[847,1083,1756,1780]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref8817" refString="Milne Edwards H (1831) Observations sur les Crustaces du genre Mithrax. Magasin de Zoologie, 2 (7): [1] - [16], pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1831">Milne Edwards, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, cannot be the type species of the genus as the species was not originally included within the genus (Article 67.2 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, hereafter the Code, 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2DABF8DF4B5CF8C3" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1180,1342,1852,1876]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" refId="ref8214" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature) (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999: 66</bibRefCitation>
, 67). Only two species were originally included in 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2DF0F8BF4B24F8E3" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1223,1350,1884,1908]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2DF0F8BF4B24F8E3" box="[1223,1350,1884,1908]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by White (1848: 222): 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2A83F89F4B75F803" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[948,1303,1916,1940]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2A83F89F4AF3F803" box="[948,1169,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys serratus</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
(from “Isle of 
<collectingCountry id="1DDE76763369FF9D2A1AF87F4D1AF823" box="[813,888,1948,1972]" name="France" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">France</collectingCountry>
” = 
<collectingCountry id="1DDE76763369FF9D2AABF87F4A6AF823" box="[924,1032,1948,1972]" name="Mauritius" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2D72F87F4BC9F823" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[1093,1451,1948,1972]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiniger">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D72F87F4B40F823" box="[1093,1314,1948,1972]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys spiniger</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
(from the 
<collectingCountry id="1DDE76763369FF9D2AAAF85F4A06F843" box="[925,1124,1980,2004]" name="Philippines" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Philippine Islands</collectingCountry>
). 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D653369FF9D2D4FF85F4D07F863" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF43369FF9D2D4FF85F4B38F843" box="[1144,1370,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="12">Schizophrys serratus</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
, is herein selected as the type species of the genus as it conforms to the current taxonomic concept of the genus (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B173369FF9D2A6EF7FF4AAAF7A3" author="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA" box="[857,1224,2076,2100]" pageId="0" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref7911" refString="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA (1986) The Decapoda Brachyura of the Siboga expedition. Part VIII: Majidae. Siboga Expeditie Monografie, 39: [i-vii], 1 - 335, pls. 1 - 22, 3 tables." type="book chapter" year="1986">Griffin &amp; Tranter, 1986: 243–245</bibRefCitation>
). Although the status of the 
<typeStatus id="BA728844336BFF9F298EFF5D4E85FF41" box="[185,231,190,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F284DFF5E4C8FFF42" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[378,749,189,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F284DFF5E4C39FF42" box="[378,603,189,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Schizophrys serratus</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
, is unknown and the figure provided (White, 1848: 223, unnumbered fig., reproduced as 
<figureCitation id="FDF22A63336BFF9F28EDFF1E4C4DFE82" box="[474,559,253,277]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[136,175,2026,2050]" captionTargetBox="[161,1449,194,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-7@1.[161,1449,189,2011]" captionText="Fig. 1. Species of Schizophrys White, 1848. A, Schizophrys serratus White, 1848 syntype (from White, 1848: 223, unnumbered fig.), “Isle of France” (= Mauritius); B, Mithrax asper H. Milne Edwards, 1831, lectotype (herein designated), female (carapace width × carapace length: 25.1 × 29.3 mm) (MNHN-IU-B463), no locality (photographed by N.K. Ng)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4776873" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4776873/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) is a small-sized specimen (probably a juvenile), the figure shows enough characters to leave no doubt about its generic affinities. The second species included by White (1848) in 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F2B50FEBE4C8BFEE2" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[615,745,349,373]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F2B50FEBE4C8BFEE2" box="[615,745,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Schizophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F2946FE9D4FE1FE02" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[113,387,381,405]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiniger">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F2946FE9D4E1CFE02" box="[113,126,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F29A6FE9D4E89FE02" box="[145,235,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">spiniger</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
, is currently considered to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F29C9FE7E4C05FE22" authority="Heller, 1861" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1861" box="[254,615,413,437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Cyclax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicinctus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F29C9FE7E4FB1FE22" box="[254,467,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Cyclax spinicinctus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="01584B17336BFF9F28EAFE7E4C05FE22" author="Heller C" box="[477,615,413,437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="297 - 374" refId="ref8080" refString="Heller C (1861) Beitrage zur Crustaceen-Fauna des rothen Meeres. Erster Theil [= Part I]. Sitzungsberichte der mathematischnaturwissenscaftlichen Classe der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Wien, 43 (1): 297 - 374, Pls. I-IV. [18 Apr. 1861]" type="journal article" year="1861">Heller, 1861</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B17336BFF9F2B91FE7E4F39FE42" author="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref7911" refString="Griffin DJG &amp; Tranter HA (1986) The Decapoda Brachyura of the Siboga expedition. Part VIII: Majidae. Siboga Expeditie Monografie, 39: [i-vii], 1 - 335, pls. 1 - 22, 3 tables." type="book chapter" year="1986">Griffin &amp; Tranter, 1986: 244</bibRefCitation>
, 246; 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B17336BFF9F28A8FE5D4C1EFE42" author="Ng PKL &amp; Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF" box="[415,636,445,470]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref9117" refString="Ng PKL, Guinot D &amp; Davie PJF (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">Ng et al., 2008: 116</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="01584B17336BFF9F2BA7FE5D4F51FE62" author="Forest J &amp; Guinot D" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="1960 - 1962" refId="ref7593" refString="Forest J &amp; Guinot D (1961) Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de Tahiti et des Tuamotu. In: Expedition Francaise sur les Recifs Coralliens de la Nouvelle-Caledonie organisee sous l'egide de la Fondation Singer-Polignac 1960 - 1962. Editions de la Fondation Singer-Polignac, Paris, vol. 1, xi + 195 pp., 13 pls. 3 tables." type="book chapter" year="1961">Forest &amp; Guinot (1961: 16</bibRefCitation>
, 17) considered 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F28DAFE3E4CB3FE62" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[493,721,477,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiniger">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F28DAFE3E4CB3FE62" box="[493,721,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Schizophrys spiniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a valid species of 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F286DFE1E4C4FFD82" authority="Dana, 1851" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[346,557,509,533]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Cyclax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F286DFE1E4FC6FD82" box="[346,420,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">Cyclax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="01584B17336BFF9F289AFE1D4C4FFD82" author="Dana JD" box="[429,557,509,533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" pagination="268 - 274" refId="ref6974" refString="Dana JD (1851) Conspectus Crustaceorum quae in Orbis Terrarum circumnavigatione, Carolo Wilkes e Classe Reipublicae Foederatae Duce. Pars VI. American Journal of Science and Arts, ser. 2, 11 (32): 268 - 274. [Published before Mar. 1851, see Anonymous (1851 a: 185).]" type="journal article" year="1851">Dana, 1851</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but regardless of the validity of the species, it is not currently regarded as congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="A2C94D65336BFF9F281EFDDD4C4FFDC2" authority="White, 1848" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1848" box="[297,557,573,597]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Schizophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F281EFDDD4F56FDC2" box="[297,308,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="57BDEAF4336BFF9F2873FDDD4FF9FDC2" box="[324,411,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="14">serratus</emphasis>
White, 1848
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
